  "prompt": "How much do furniture salesmen make?",
  "response": "The earnings of furniture salesmen can vary widely based on several factors, including location, experience, the specific employer, and whether they earn a base salary, commission, or a combination of both.\n\nOn average, furniture salesmen in the United States can earn between $30,000 and $50,000 per year. However, those who are highly successful or work in high-end furniture stores can earn more, sometimes exceeding $60,000 or even $70,000 annually. Additionally, commissions can play a significant role in their overall compensation, with some salesmen earning a substantial portion of their income through sales commissions.\n\nBenefits such as health insurance, retirement plans, and employee discounts can also contribute to the overall compensation package. It\u2019s important to note that these figures can vary significantly depending on the specific circumstances and the performance of the individual salesperson.",
